==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lacustrine
<hw>La*cus"trine</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>lacus</ets> lake: cf.
F. <ets>lacustral</ets>, <ets>lacustre</ets>.]</ety> <def>Found in, or
pertaining to, lakes or ponds, or growing in them; <as>as,
<ex>lacustrine</ex> flowers</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Lacustrine deposits</b></col> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>, <cd>the
deposits which have been accumulated in fresh-water areas.</cd> --
<col><b>Lacustrine dwellings</b></col>. <cd>See <cref>Lake
dwellings</cref>, under <er>Lake</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

